Interface Interactable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    Fire, FishingSpot, Goblin, Mob, MoltenCorki, Rat, Skeleton, Tree, WorldChanger

    public interface Interactable
    The Interactable interface should be implemented by any class whose instances can interact with the player. This means that those objects can respond to the player.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void respond()
      This method defines how the object responds to the player.

    • Method Detail

      • respond

        void respond()
        This method defines how the object responds to the player. Each type of object has its own way to respond
